quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,40,"It is not for the sun to overtake the moon, nor does the night outstrip the day. They all float, each in an orbit."
  36,41,"And an Ayâh (sign) for them is that We bore their offspring in the laden ship [of Nûh (Noah)]."
  36,42,"And We have created for them of the like thereunto, on which they ride."
  37,25,""
  37,26,"Nay, but that Day they shall surrender."
  37,27,"And they will turn to one another and question one another."
  38,4,"And they (Arab pagans) wonder that a warner (Prophet Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) has come to them from among themselves. And the disbelievers say: "
  38,5,""
  38,6,"And the leaders among them went about (saying): "